# Vendored (lightly reformatted) from
# https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/socrates/socrates.n3
# EYE's own query for this case is the fully-generic
# "{ ?WHO a ?WHAT } => { ?WHO a ?WHAT }" (i.e. "select every rdf:type fact
# from the closure"), so EYE's own answer file
# (reasoning/socrates/socrates-answer.n3) IS the full closure for this
# predicate, matching what materialize() computes directly.
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix : <http://example.org/socrates#>.

:Socrates a :Human.
:Human rdfs:subClassOf :Mortal.

{
    ?A rdfs:subClassOf ?B.
    ?S a ?A.
} => {
    ?S a ?B.
}.
